Operatives of the Kaduna State Police have arrested a serving councilor with an AK-47 with rounds of 7.62 X 39mm live ammunition in Soba Local Government Area, LGA, of Kaduna State. NAN reports that according to a statement issued by the Command’s Public Relations Officer, PPRO, Muhammad Jalige, “Operatives Operation Puff Adder II attached to the Kaduna Police Command, acting on the instruction of CP Yekini Ayoku on May 9, at about 0800hrs conducted routine patrol along Galadimawa road Giwa LGA of Kaduna State. “The operation is aimed at ensuring sanity on the connecting axis succeeded in intercepting a Lifan motorcycle, ridden by one by the suspect. -Advertisement- “Upon a search, a concealed AK47 rifle loaded with six rounds of 7.62 X 39mm live ammunition were recovered from the sack and taken into custody alongside the suspect. “The suspect equally confessed to have gotten the firearm from his accomplices and he is to deliver same to bandits around Galadimawa village for their nefarious activities,” he added. The CP, however, appreciated the diligence and thoroughness exhibited by the officers, adding that a full-scale investigation will be carried out to ensure all those connected with the said crime are apprehended to face justice.